  "articleSummary": "**Summary**  \nThe article argues that modern developer workstations are high‑value attack surfaces and that “being careful” is insufficient; instead, security must be built into the environment so that a single compromised action has a limited blast radius. It proposes a six‑step blueprint—Isolate work in DevContainers, limit mounts, scope secrets, plant canarytokens, delay fresh package installs (e.g., pnpm’s minimumReleaseAge), and respond quickly by rotating keys and following a runbook. The piece is a practical, tutorial‑style guide aimed at software engineers, DevOps teams, and security‑conscious developers, using the metaphor of a “credential cruise ship” and recurring imagery of “canaries” and “boxes” to frame the defensive measures.",
